bdsimjob.sh is the actual script that runs for each job. It takes in many variables
as arguments which can be used in the command(s) it runs.

htcondor.sub is the submission file that specifies the input variables as well as
the number of jobs to submit.

How to submit:

condor_submit htcondor.sub

NOTE - paths and variables will need to be changed in both files for wherever your
installation is. These are provided as an example. It is recommend to use the absolute
path to the input files where possible as it may execute from a different location. The
memory and disk requirements should be adjusted as required for each study.